e in order to experiment with and implement methods according to their own needs and situations. The practices are divided thematically and include, among others, methods for decentering, improving transparency, and increasing inclusivity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aAnthropology. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aColonialism and imperialism. 4aContemporary History. 4aCultural Studies. 4aCultural studies. 4aHeritage Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aMuseology and heritage studies. 4ac 1500 onwards to present day. 7aART / Museum Studies.2bisacsh  aDecolonisation, Museums, Practices, Global, Accessible.1 aAriese, Csilla E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aE. Ariese, Csilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWróblewska, Magdalena, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWróblewska, Magdalena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048554836?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048554836zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048554836/original  a978-3-11-074322-7 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA